{"key":"post-8954814","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>8954814</id>\n<content>Yes, treat uncased substrates as cakes, which by definition are uncased substrates.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;You can easily dunk a bulk substrate.&amp;nbsp; I prefer to do it under the faucet with very gently running water so that the tray overflows and the excess runs down the drain.&amp;nbsp; Weigh the substrate with whatever you have to set on top to hold it down. A mason jar or two full of water works well.&amp;nbsp; The moving water seems to help re-hydration and it also washes away contaminant spores.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>8955069</next>\n<prev>8954791</prev>\n<first>8954791</first>\n<last>8955069</last>\n<when>1221851830</when>\n<utime>09/19/08 10:17 PM</utime>\n</post>"}